></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Detailed below are Defra’s responses to the questions raised at the Select Committee Hearing on 22nd October 2013 as detailed in the email from the Second Clerk. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">EA staff costs – what are Other Staff related costs? How much of the £30 m increase to staff costs is covered by the additional funding for flood defences?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Other staff related costs comprise primarily of staff allowances and pension contributions to the closed pension scheme. The contributions to the active pension scheme are categorised separately in note 3. The Agency intends to categorise the closed pension payments separately in the next ARA to enhance the reader’s understanding. The staff allowances include standby and call out payments for frontline staff relating to flood incident management. In addition, other staff costs include small </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">discretionary payments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> made to staff not entitled to overtime or unsociable hour payments in recognition of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">substantial contributions made to incident management.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The £30m staff cost increase arose primarily </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> delivery of specialist frontline </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">non flood </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">projects, as well as flood incident management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in 2012</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, with a lower proportion corresponding with the increased flood defence funding which was largely capital expenditure. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This was funded through the additional budget provided to the Agency during the year.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">How many Off-payroll staff does Defra still have, at what cost? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We assume that this question is related to the disclosure of the tax arrangements of public sector appointees, ARA page 37. The Treasury review of the tax arrangements of public sector appointees (published 23 May 2012) requested information from central government departments and their arm’s length bodies, in relation to all individuals engaged off payroll as of 31 January 2012, where the cost to the department is in excess of £58,200 per annum (the Senior Civil Service minimum).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Defra's review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">identified </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">144 off-payroll engagements that were in place </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 31 January 2012. With the exception of 3 individuals, all either left or Defra renegotiated their contract to be compliant with HMT requirements. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The current position is that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">two </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">individual</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">provided assurance for the relevant period</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">third</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> person </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">left</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Defra in June 2013</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Treasury required these contracts to be amended only to the extent that the work involved represented value for money for the taxpayer.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">hy has the cost of fees and commissions almost doubled? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The amount charged to administration costs in 2012-13 was £17m, 2011-12 £9m. This increase of £8m was mainly due to:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">£2m for payments to the Treasury Solicitors’ Department for a full year in 2012-13, as opposed to only 8 months in the previous year since the start of the new</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arrangement for legal services. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">£6m costs for compensation payments </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">made by the Environment Agency (using income from the Environmental Improvement Unit Charge) for abstraction licences that were varied or revoked.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Why did Defra make an additional payment to NuStar (£413,000) in 2012-13</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The original payment made reflected the outcome of the contractual</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dispute</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> between RPA and NuStar, which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was formally settled at mediation under the terms of a full and final settlement. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A further special payment of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">£413,000 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> made in 2012-13 related to RPA’s agreed contribution towards the final outstanding site cleanup costs.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  This was cleared through HM Treasury.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>